  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5234",
  "title": "Setting `initialUiState` for a custom widget (negativeRefinementList) throws an exception",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nI followed the docs [here](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/widgets/create-your-own-widgets/react-hooks/?client=TypeScript) to build a negative refinement list widget, the article is clear and the widget is working as expected, except when I needed to have one item selected by default (or when I try to use routing).\r\n\r\nTo make an item selected by default I'm passing an `initialUiState` to `<InstantSearch.. ` component like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\ninitialUiState={{\r\n  demo: {\r\n    negativeRefinementList: {\r\n      categories: [\"Technology\"]\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the app is rendered I get the following error: \r\n> Unhandled Runtime Error TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'categories')\r\n\r\nSource\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Create a custom widget\r\n2. Use the widget\r\n3. Set InitialUiState for the widget\r\n4. See error\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\nhttps://replit.com/@FarisAbusada/InstantSearchCustomWidget#pages/index.tsx\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\n\"Technology\" checkbox to be selected by default\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\n![screenshot- 2022-12-13 at 15 03 11@2x](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2572320/207353344-fdd8346f-d0eb-456a-9e21-f0ab6e4f5ed4.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- React InstantSearch version: 6.38.1\r\n- React version: \"18.2.0\"\r\n\r\n",
